      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why Q-Containing Words Matter in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>Q is worth 10 points — the maximum tile value in Scrabble — but it's also the most dangerous tile to hold. If you can't play it, those 10 points become a 10-point penalty at game end. The difference between a player who knows Q words and one who doesn't is enormous: the first deploys Q for 20+ point plays, while the second gets stuck exchanging or eating the penalty.</p>
      <p>The Q-without-U words are game-changers. QI (11 points for 2 letters) is the most efficient Q play and works in parallel positions constantly. QOPH, QADI, and QAID give you options when U is unavailable. Combined with standard Q+U words like QUARTZ (24 points), SQUEEZE (25 points), and TRANQUIL (17 points), knowing a broad Q vocabulary means you'll never be stuck holding the most valuable tile in the bag without a play.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
