        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Memorise Q-without-U words:</strong> QI, QOPH, QADI, QAID, QANAT, QINTAR, QWERTY — these save you when U isn't on your rack. QI alone wins more games than any other Q word.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Don't hold Q too long:</strong> If you can't play Q within 2-3 turns, consider exchanging. A 10-point penalty at game end is worse than losing one turn to exchange.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>QUARTZ is the gold standard:</strong> At 24 points with common tiles (Q, U, A, R, T, Z), QUARTZ uses both Q and Z in one play. Look for this whenever you hold both premium tiles.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Use QI for parallel plays:</strong> QI fits next to almost any word on the board. Place Q on a premium square and form QI crossing an existing word for massive multi-word scores.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Keep U when Q is in the bag:</strong> Track whether Q has been played. If it hasn't, hold at least one U tile as insurance against drawing Q without a play.</span></li>
      </ul>

